Some gunmen have abducted some students of the Federal University of Agriculture, Makurdi (FUAM) in Benue State. The school authorities confirmed the incident to Daily Trust, saying an unspecified number of students were taken away at gunpoint on Sunday night. SaharaReporters Media  The Director of Information, Protocol and Public Relations Unit (IPPR), Mrs Rosemary Waku, made the disclosure on Monday. Just last week, an unspecified number of students were kidnapped at Greenfield University, a private tertiary institution in Kaduna State. The bodies of three of the abducted students were later found close to the school.